transcript.text: Welcome to On Print Shop.
In today's video, we'll guide you through creating and managing admin group roles, making it easy for you to grant access to any users.
Inside the On Print Shop admin panel, you have the power to provide admin access to team members or any users.
So let's break down and understand the process step by step.
Defining Roles To get started, you'll need to define roles for your admin groups.
Imagine you have a marketing team.
They'll need access to certain parts of the admin panel like products, content management, and SEO modules.
Once you've assigned these modules, just save the changes.
Creating a group Go back to the main page.
There you'll see the group you created with the designated roles.
Assigning Group Roles Now it's time to assign these roles to a specific person, so head to the Admin section and hit the Add button.
Choose the store and assign the person to the Marketing team group.
Provide their username, password, and e-mail ID.
Super Admin versus Sub Admin The next decision is whether they should be a Super admin or a Sub admin.
A Super admin has access to everything, while a Sub admin has limited access.
To make someone a super admin, enable the button for a Sub Admin.
Keep it disabled.
Activate and notify the admin.
Don't forget to activate the admin status.
You can also choose to notify the person by enabling the setting.
This way, they'll be acknowledged by their login credentials through e-mail verification.
To verify or check the admin and access granted, log into the admin's account.
You can see that the Marketing team admin has access to the product, content management and SEO sections only.
And that's it.
Isn't it easy?
You've successfully created a group role and an admin account with the desired level of access.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
